Ready state maps to OCI ACTIVE or INACTIVE.
Requeue continues while OCI reports CREATING,
UPDATING, or DELETING.
Bind-before-create reuses only exact
compartment, availability-domain, and
display-name matches that remain in ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, or INACTIVE.
Create, update, and delete are
work-request-backed, but steady-state readiness
is still classified from Lustre file system
lifecycle state.
Delete completes after GetLustreFileSystem or
ListLustreFileSystems returns DELETED or no
longer finds the resource.
